Absolutely not. While AI excels at handling routine queries quickly and efficiently, it fundamentally struggles with the nuance and emotional depth that often defines customer experiences, particularly in critical or sensitive interactions. By integrating both AI and human agents, companies like Klarna can create a more balanced and effective customer support model.

